title: Chapter 1793 - A Dragon Returns To The Sea
body:
Chapter 1793 - A Dragon Returns To The Sea

A petite figure flew beneath the dome of heaven. She flashed past like a fleeting beam of light, leaving no trace whatsoever.

The young woman looked up and gazed into the distance. That’s Evening Fog City up ahead!

She was dressed in broad-sleeved, black clothing, and her face was fair and tender. The staunch determination on her face seemed out of place given her youthful features.

Her bright golden eyes were particularly attention-grabbing, and her flowing long hair shone with a faint hint of red beneath the light of the heavens, like fleeting glimpses of fire.

She had an extraordinary disposition, too: cold and aloof, like solitary, never-melting ice. Despite her petite frame, her every gesture was dignified and contemptuous, as if she were gazing down upon all living things.

This was an imposing might originating from her bloodline. It could intimidate all other living beings!

Suddenly, the young woman saw a figure exit the distant Evening Fog City. He was headed her way. He was dressed in plain Daoist robes, and he wore his hair in a topknot. He had a clear, refreshing air about him, as if he’d risen out of the dust of mundanity,...
